The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, July 14, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Monday, July 14, 2003				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Lower Circular Road, between Camac Street and Lansdowne Road, due to work on AJC Bose Road flyover. Buses heading towards Alipore zoo will take the Lansdowne Road-Elgin Road-Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Chowringhee-Queensway-Hospital Road-Lower Circular Road route. Those travelling towards Beckbagan will take the Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Hazra Road-Ballygunge Phari-Syed Amir Ali Avenue route.				 																Talk				 																																	A discussion on the practical aspects of scientific and eco-friendly waste management systems, organised by Disha, at Bangla Akademi, 3 pm.				 																Films				 																																	Rodney Bennets Hamlet will be screened, as part of Tragedies  A festival of Shakespeare in Film, at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre at 5 pm.				 																																	A special screening of Krzysztof Kieslowskis trilogy Three Colours  Blue, White, Red, presented by Cine Central, at Mahajati Sadan from 4 pm.				 																Art watch				 																																	An exhibition of contemporary Indian Art at Gallery Caps.
